  "summary": "Benchmark-only TLS I/O counters were isolated behind the opt-in bench_tls_io feature and exercised on a short three-scenario phase diagnostic. Canonical libcurl_bench builds compile without bench_tls_io, so the fair matrix does not pay diagnostic counter overhead. The diagnostic data still refutes TLS wrapper poll explosion as a SOTA-scale bottleneck: HTTP over HTTPS proxy averages 2 SSL reads and 1 SSL-read pending per request; HTTPS origin over HTTPS proxy and proxy-mTLS HTTPS origin average 5 SSL reads and 2 SSL-read pendings per request. Response-read time still dominates response-head time, so the remaining bottleneck is consistent with sequential HTTP/1 request/response wait and runtime/TLS wakeup cost rather than excessive wrapper loops.",
